  "prompt": "How do you convert moles to atm?",
  "response": "To convert moles to atmospheres (atm), you need to use the ideal gas law: PV = nRT\n\nWhere:\nP = Pressure (atm)\nV = Volume (liters)\nn = Number of moles\nR = Gas constant (0.0821 L\u22c5atm/mol\u22c5K)\nT = Temperature (Kelvin)\n\nSteps to convert:\n1. Rearrange the ideal gas law to solve for P: P = (nRT)/V\n2. Plug in the known values:\n   - Number of moles (n)\n   - Temperature (T) in Kelvin\n   - Volume (V) in liters\n   - Use R = 0.0821 L\u22c5atm/mol\u22c5K\n\nExample:\nIf you have 2 moles of gas at 300 K in a 10 L container:\nP = (2 mol \u00d7 0.0821 L\u22c5atm/mol\u22c5K \u00d7 300 K) / 10 L\n  = 49.26 atm\n\nNote: This method assumes ideal gas behavior.",
